czPjeq0UdahiRrn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recWYK5Vj3YfsLOii","target":"recCXgnK86jc1U9IB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recWYK5Vj3YfsLOii","target":"recQ1bj3p4Lj5MYY6","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recHWfYpBj3fnZIQu","ref":"Isa.40.1","text":"Comfort ye, comfort ye my people, saith your God.","year":-712},{"id":"recUBnyQY2rxFNbHE","ref":"Isa.40.2","text":"Speak ye comfortably to Jerusalem, and cry unto her, that her warfare is accomplished, that her iniquity is pardoned: for she hath received of the LORD’S hand double for all her sins.","year":-712},{"id":"rec3ncbh5qui9VnNx","ref":"Isa.40.3","text":"The voice of him that crieth in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the LORD, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.","year":-712},{"id":"recivGpTvZI6DbLE0","ref":"Isa.40.4","text":"Every valley shall be exalted, and every mountain and hill shall be made low: and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough places plain:","year":-712},{"id":"recYOcYfVe6X0mCdG","ref":"Isa.40.5","text":"And the glory of the LORD shall be revealed, and all flesh shall see it together: for the mouth of the LORD hath spoken it.","year":-712},{"id":"recrgtD9Ep9xubIhj","ref":"Isa.40.6","text":"The voice said, Cry. And he said, What shall I cry? All flesh is grass, and all the goodliness thereof is as the flower of the field:","year":-712},{"id":"recRf5BG7gCi7s7UV","ref":"Isa.40.7","text":"The grass withereth, the flower fadeth: because the spirit of the LORD bloweth upon it: surely the people is grass.","year":-712},{"id":"recBPwrTuhXVbkK7l","ref":"Isa.40.8","text":"The grass withereth, the flower fadeth: but the word of our God shall stand for ever.","year":-712}]}
